wikipedia_page.main: James Francis Oswald (1838–1908) was a British politician. He was elected as a Conservative Member of Parliament for Oldham in 1895, resigning in 1899 by becoming Steward of the Manor of Northstead.

link_mentions.page: List of MPs elected in the 1895 United Kingdom general election
